            <title>[HBASE-8595] Add rename operation in hbase shell</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8595</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We can use a set of snapshot commands to elegantly rename a table. It would be nice to wrap all those commands in a single call.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://hbase.apache.org/book.html#table.rename&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hbase.apache.org/book.html#table.rename&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also &amp;#8211; the documentation is missing the last step where the original table needs to be deleted. I can add that to the docbook.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
