                            <comment id="13704362" author="mbertozzi" created="Wed, 10 Jul 2013 09:39:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I really don&apos;t like the rename implemented with the snapshot. &lt;br/&gt;
It&apos;s fine if you don&apos;t have other choices and you know what you&apos;re doing.&lt;br/&gt;
but snapshots are not free and if you rename a table using snapshots you loose the possibility  to use your distcp scripts to backup the table, unless you trigger major compaction to get rid of the links.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the patch posted here is more for people who wants to have an easy way to rename a table with a single shell command, instead of typing the 5 commands in the doc book.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
